https://baseball.atlassian.net/browse/EBISII-19025 was caused by old logic that is still present on both the ppph and ppp services on the UI as well as some logic that exists on the backend.

The backend currently sets flags and fills in beans to indicate whether the player has domestic or intl amateur info.  Its also checking against the OLD ama_player, dom_ama_entry' and probalby intl_ama_entry tables.  That needs to be cleaned up, those tables should not be referenced in ebis any longer.

The front end then checks to see if the returned player object has an amateur bean populated and tries to pull the players name from there.  In this case, it didnt exist at all, so there was nothing to display.

The following SQLs will put the bad records back for Ramos (employee in the above JIRA) so that we can work through this mess appropriately.

